Package chav1961.purelib.basic

Interface FSM.FSMCallback<Terminal extends java.lang.Enum<?>,​NonTerminal extends java.lang.Enum<?>,​Exit extends java.lang.Enum<?>,​Parameter>

Type Parameters:
Terminal - terminal (in the terms of FSM)
NonTerminal - non-terminal (in the terms of FSM)
Exit - exit symbol (in the terms of FSM)
Parameter - any cargo to pass thru the FSM to FSM callback
Enclosing class:
FSM<Terminal extends java.lang.Enum<?>,​NonTerminal extends java.lang.Enum<?>,​Exit extends java.lang.Enum<?>,​Parameter>
Functional Interface:
This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
@FunctionalInterface
public static interface FSM.FSMCallback<Terminal extends java.lang.Enum<?>,​NonTerminal extends java.lang.Enum<?>,​Exit extends java.lang.Enum<?>,​Parameter>

This interface describes a callback to process successful FSM state changes.

Since:
0.0.2

    • process

      void process​(FSM<Terminal,​NonTerminal,​Exit,​Parameter> fsm, Terminal terminal, NonTerminal fromState, NonTerminal toState, Exit[] action, Parameter parameter) throws FlowException

      Process callback of the FSM

      Parameters:
      fsm - fsm instance that calls this method
      terminal - terminal from the FSM.processTerminal(Enum, Object) method
      fromState - current state of the FSM
      toState - new state of the FSM
      action - action list for the given state jump
      parameter - parameter from the FSM.processTerminal(Enum, Object) method
      Throws:
      FlowException - indicate any processing errors
